<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFE0FFC49A07FAC3F8F0354F" box="[634,689,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2002), to Monterey Bay, central California (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFE0FFC49CE0FAC2FB43356B" author="Eschmeyer and Herald" firstAuthor="Eschmeyer" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" refId="ref277744" refString="Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; Herald, E. S. (1983) A Field Guide to Pacific Coast Fishes of North America from the Gulf of Alaska to Baja California. Houghton Mifflin, Boston." type="book" year="1983">Eschmeyer and Herald 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Depth: juveniles and young adults to about 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFE0FFC49A85FAA6F908356A" box="[760,841,1364,1391]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="cm" value="110.0">110 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFE0FFC49B25FAA6F9D2356A" box="[856,915,1364,1391]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0922" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="in" value="43.0">43 in</quantity>
) TL collected near surface, sometimes close to shore (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFE0FFC499CDFA8BFBA83597" box="[432,489,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2002); adults close to bottom; depth: 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFE0FFC49BE5FA8AFE6C3596" box="[920,1069,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.235" metricValueMax="10.47" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="m" value="623.5" valueMax="1047.0" valueMin="200.0">200–1,047 m</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFE0FFC49C41FA8AFE933596" box="[1084,1234,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.239256" metricValueMax="10.479023999999999" metricValueMin="1.999488" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="ft" value="2047.0" valueMax="3438.0" valueMin="656.0">656–3,438 ft</quantity>
), usually far from shore (min.: Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFE0FFC4998DFA6FF86935B3" box="[496,552,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2002; max.: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFE0FFC49AC1FA6EF9D635B3" author="Zolotov" box="[700,919,1436,1462]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Zolotov" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" pagination="251 - 265" refId="ref335189" refString="Zolotov, O. G., Spirin, I. Yu. &amp; Zudina, S. M. (2014) New data on the range, biology, and abundance of skilfish Erilepis zonifer (Anoplopomatidae). Journal of Ichthyology, 54, 251 - 265. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / s 0032945214020131" type="journal article" year="2014">
Zolotov 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFE0FFC49B66FA6FF91535B3" box="[795,852,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
